text: Christiaan Eijkman (August 11, 1858 - November 5, 1930) was a Dutch doctor. He won the 1929 Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine, along with Sir Frederick Hopkins, for the discovery of vitamins == References == Category:1858 births Category:1930 deaths Category:Dutch academics Category:Dutch Nobel Prize winners Category:Dutch physicians
